reviewText: If someone said that at the time of this video, it was Willie Nelson at his prime, I'd simply smile and say nothing.  Willie is Willie, from the time I first became a fan,the summer of 1972 to today, Willie is always "at his prime".  But, this video is especially significant since it was recorded in Austin for Austin City Limits which always had great audiences with a real appreciation of Willie and his music.  Great selection of songs and great band musicians.
summary: What can you say, it's WILLIE

reviewText: This is outstanding from beginning to end period!!!!  This concert was recorded/filmed September 6, 1990. You get 17 great songs, including classics such as: "Whiskey River", "Good-Hearted Woman", Medley of "Funny-Crazy-Night Life", "If You've Got the Money Honey", "Me & Bobby McGee", "Loving Her was Easier", "Bloody Mary Morning", "Blue Eyes Cring in the Rain",  "On the Road Again", "Always on my mind" and others.He has a great 9 piece band, including his sister on the piano. This is a true classic, and a "must-have" for any Willie Nelson fan period!!!!
summary: Willie Nelson - "Live from Austin, Texas"  "From the Legend Himself" "The Man Who Started it All, Down in Austin"!!!!!!

reviewText: It's always great to hear Willie sing his classics, 'cause he never really sings them the same way twice!And that's how it was in this great concert from Austin. Willie changed up his vocals enough so everything sounded fresh and new.As always, his guitar playing was admirable.The concert is a little short, with a running time of just 59 minutes. But hey, I could listen to Willie sing all night long!Despite my Wille Greed, and wanting the concert to last a little longer, this was a terrific way to hear a lot of old favorites from Willie.There are 17 songs on the DVD including:Whiskey RiverStay a Little LongerBlue Eyes Crying in the RainBloody Mary MorningEtc., Etc.It's a keeper that will make any Willie Nelson fan happy.
summary: Stay All Night, Stay a Little Longer
